The paper deals with explaining the predictions of a recurrent neural network used for sentiment analysis, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a specific propagation rule for multiplicative connections in recurrent network architectures, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the results quantitatively, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (NA). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a bi-directional LSTM model, which falls under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (CVPR). Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category.
